post_text:
Parents and Students:
Thanks to a USDA free meal waiver, Providence Hall Charter School will begin offering meals at no cost to all enrolled students beginning Thursday, Sept 10th at all locations. No students will be charged for breakfast or lunch through the month of December.

All schools will serve free meals in the school cafeteria. Online or Flex students will be able to continue to order meals a week in advance and pick-up accordingly at your students' school location.

For any additional questions, please reach out to our Food Service Director, Mapu Weiss, at mweiss@providencehall.com

Student Council is super excited to have our Welcome Back Assembly on 9/4 from 12:30pm to 1:10pm. We will be livestreaming the event on Instagram check it out at @phallstuco.

Parents and guests in the past we have always welcomed you to attend and support your students. Regretfully, we will not be able to do that with this assembly. We hope that you understand that due to size limitations and social distancing requirements there will not be available seating. We look forward to the time that we can all be together again. We encourage you to watch the assembly on Instagram live.

Thank you for your continued support and understanding,

post_text:
Additional online courses have been added for the 2020-2021 school year.

Students who choose online education will choose up to 7 of these courses.

Students who choose a hybrid education will choose up to 1-6 online courses and 1-7 in person courses (this process will be sent in another survey at a later date). Your students schedule will depend on what they choose to take in-person. We will try to make this schedule easy for parents (morning classes, afternoon classes, or only A day classes); however, this schedule will depend on what your student chooses and how badly they want to take a course. A hybrid education may not be possible for every family.
text:
Additional online courses have been added for the 2020-2021 school year.

Students who choose online education will choose up to 7 of these courses.

Students who choose a hybrid education will choose up to 1-6 online courses and 1-7 in person courses (this process will be sent in another survey at a later date). Your students schedule will depend on what they choose to take in-person. We will try to make this schedule easy for parents (morning classes, afternoon classes, or only A day classes); however, this schedule will depend on what your student chooses and how badly they want to take a course. A hybrid education may not be possible for every family.

post_text:
Below is more information regarding a Hybrid education for the 2020-2021 school year.

For scheduling purposes students will choose in-person courses they would like to take, and the school will schedule these requests as best as we can. We will also coordinate schedules with the JH for students with siblings.

Please understand that the in-person courses you may choose are assigned a time that may not work for your family. These courses cannot be moved to accommodate individual requests. Additionally, class sizes will be limited to maintain physical distancing. For these reasons a hybrid student's in-person course options may be reduced.

IEPs and 504s will be followed no matter which educational pathway has been chosen. Students on an IEP should discuss their pathway and course requests with their case managers.

Please complete the survey to request your students educational pathway. For those who choose online or a hybrid education please wait for additional instruction.
text:
Below is more information regarding a Hybrid education for the 2020-2021 school year.

For scheduling purposes students will choose in-person courses they would like to take, and the school will schedule these requests as best as we can. We will also coordinate schedules with the JH for students with siblings.

Please understand that the in-person courses you may choose are assigned a time that may not work for your family. These courses cannot be moved to accommodate individual requests. Additionally, class sizes will be limited to maintain physical distancing. For these reasons a hybrid student's in-person course options may be reduced.

IEPs and 504s will be followed no matter which educational pathway has been chosen. Students on an IEP should discuss their pathway and course requests with their case managers.

Please complete the survey to request your students educational pathway. For those who choose online or a hybrid education please wait for additional instruction.

Have you visualized a school with concurrent enrollment, Career Technical Ed, IB classes, and Advanced Placement offerings?

Excellence and success start with being given opportunities and support.

Give your student the chance to excel in the classroom as well as to make the most of their talents.

Providence Hall provides that supportive, small-school environment, along with extracurricular opportunities to build towards the future.

Student success and opportunity are central to Providence Hall Charter School.

Pictures IDs are required.

Pencils and calculators will be provided.

post_text:
At Providence Hall Charter School, understanding your child is vital.

That’s why your student will be in a small class.

Low student numbers allow teachers to know your child personally.

Teachers can then guide your student to the activities that are just right for them.

Your child will follow their own unique path of development.

Our individualized environment and learning tools empower your child to progressively challenge their own abilities.

This allows them to achieve more than you ever thought possible.

Discover the benefits of significantly more individual attention at Providence Hall Charter School.

post_text: Ladies and Gentleman of Providence Hall! Are you ready for Valentine's Day? Spread the love through the halls this year through the National Honors Society's Val-O-Grams. These are gifts and cards you can give to your friends and lovers! At lunch all week there will a table to buy these things that will then be delivered at the end of the week! Some items include roses, custom cards done in calligraphy, cards with candy, and EVEN being serenaded with a song by our lovely choir. You don't want to miss out! Check for prices at the table this week. All proceeds will be donated to the Utah Domestic Violence Coalition, to help stop domestic violence! Come on Patriots, let's spread the love!

post_text:
THE GIVING TREE
The National Honor Society at PHHS is in charge of the Giving Tree this year. It is our goal to try to make the holidays a little bit brighter for those in need. However, we need your help to make this a reality.
The NHS students have decorated a tree in the front office of the high school with dozens of “gift” cards they have made. These cards have an item on them that can be purchased and donated back to the school. Once all the items have been collected, we will deliver them to individuals in the PH community in need. You can do the following to be a part of this great service project:
1. Go to the office and pick a “gift” card off the tree
2. Sign out the card on the card sheet
3. Purchase the item
4. Attach the “gift” card to the item
5. Give the item and its card to the ladies in the front office

Thank you so much! Happy Holidays!

post_text:
Our school participates in the Career and technology education program through the Utah State Department of Education. We currently offer full CTE pathways in health science, computer science, law enforcement, foods and nutrition, and business and marketing. We are looking for parents to serve on our CTE panel to provide feedback and information on industry standards that can help align/improve our classes so they are more in line with industry. If you have experience or expertise in any of these areas, we would like you to participate. Please sign up using the following link if you are interested in helping:
https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSfV7CFzT8ivfpkYpi7MrmvMKhEKOavVYhTuvAr2VX_plHaRNQ/viewform
shared_text:
DOCS.GOOGLE.COM
CTE Pathway parent participation
text:
Our school participates in the Career and technology education program through the Utah State Department of Education. We currently offer full CTE pathways in health science, computer science, law enforcement, foods and nutrition, and business and marketing. We are looking for parents to serve on our CTE panel to provide feedback and information on industry standards that can help align/improve our classes so they are more in line with industry. If you have experience or expertise in any of these areas, we would like you to participate. Please sign up using the following link if you are interested in helping:
https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSfV7CFzT8ivfpkYpi7MrmvMKhEKOavVYhTuvAr2VX_plHaRNQ/viewform

Attention PHHS Parents and Students,

We wanted to inform you that the High School had a water leak that was caused by damage done to one of our exit pipes during today's storm. The water was confined only to the cafeteria.

We currently have crews on scene to clean up the water and repair the damaged areas. School will resume as normal tomorrow and have a plan to accommodate school lunch.

Thank you for your patience.
